---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ResonantDAO - Membership, Reputation, Governance" description="ResonantDAO is the Community of Communities layer for ResonantOS, governed through verified membership, contribution reputation, and elected custodians.">
	<section class="px-4 pb-16 pt-14 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
			<p class="mb-5 font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-400">ResonantDAO</p>
			<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">A Community of Communities, governed by contribution.</h1>
			<p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-8 text-zinc-300">
				ResonantDAO is the governance and membership layer for ResonantOS. Its first job is simple: create official, verifiable membership credentials that other DAO contracts can trust.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Governance Model</h2>
			<div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<p class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400">Layer 1</p>
					<h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Community Members</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">Base DAO participants with an active Community Member NFT and official MemberRecord.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<p class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400">Layer 2</p>
					<h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Reputation Holders</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">Members who earn levels and domain reputation through contribution, not capital alone.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<p class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400">Layer 3</p>
					<h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Custodians</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">Operational stewards elected and replaceable by the community as the DAO matures.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Bootstrap Phase</h2>
				<p class="mt-4 text-zinc-400">
					The DAO begins with a practical bootstrap phase so work can move quickly. Manolo Remiddi is the first custodian, but this is a temporary starting condition, not the final governance model.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Human and AI Members</h2>
				<p class="mt-4 text-zinc-400">
					Human Community Members and future AI Community Members should be separate credentials. Humans govern. AI agents can participate economically and operationally without pretending to be human voters.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl rounded-lg border border-amber-400/20 bg-amber-400/[0.06] p-6">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Token Economy Status</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 text-zinc-300">
				Earlier ResonantOS drafts described contribution tokens, stable-growth tokens, marketplaces, and APY mechanics. Those remain conceptual and are not the current implementation focus. The current foundation is membership, originality, access control, contribution reputation, and governance safety.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
